@startuml seq-review-freeze
!include tarifhub-style.iuml

' Runtime view: how a flagged record becomes a new immutable version.
' Render: plantuml docs/diagrams/seq-review-freeze.puml (done in a later phase)

title Runtime view: review → freeze loop (design level, ADR-013)
caption <color:#64748b>Flagged record → expert decision → new immutable version. freeze(), audit and flagging are live; the review surface is designed.</color>

actor "Tariff expert" as expert
participant "TarifGuard console\n(review form, designed)" as console <<designed>>
participant "Review API\n(ingestion, designed)" as api <<designed>>
participant "Validator + scorer" as validator
participant "freeze()\nversioning/freeze_record.py" as freeze
participant "AuditLogger" as audit
database "PostgreSQL" as db

note over expert, api #f8fafc
  <color:#475569>Precondition (live today): the pipeline froze this record with
  requires_review = true (harmonization_confidence < 0.85,
  TARIFHUB_REVIEW_THRESHOLD); it sits flagged in the review queue.</color>
end note

expert -> console : open flagged record\n(master-detail view)
console -> api : fetch record + confidence detail
api --> console : record, scores, review flags
expert -> console : submit correction / approval\n(review form)
console -> api : POST review decision

api -> validator : re-validate (validate + score)
validator --> api : ValidationResult + confidence

alt decision = approve
  api -> freeze : freeze(corrected record)
  freeze -> freeze : SHA-256 record_hash over sorted\ncanonical content; re-freezing a frozen\nrecord raises ValueError
  freeze -> db : INSERT: NEW immutable version\n(supersedes the flagged one)
  api -> audit : append review_decision + freeze events
  audit -> db : INSERT audit_log rows (append-only)
  api --> console : frozen: record leaves the review queue
else decision = reject / needs rework
  api -> audit : append review_decision event
  audit -> db : INSERT audit_log row (append-only)
  api --> console : record stays in the review queue
end

note over freeze, audit #fffbeb
  <color:#b45309>guard-protected: versioning/ and audit/ are write-protected
  against AI edits (guard_frozen hook); the freeze line is enforced
  by AST boundary tests.</color>
end note

note over console, api #f8fafc
  <color:#475569>Console form + review endpoint are ADR-013 design scope,
  not yet implemented; freeze(), audit and flagging are live today
  (exercised by the pipeline).</color>
end note

@enduml
